==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Seediness
<hw>Seed`i*ness</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or
state of being seedy, shabby, or worn out; a state of wretchedness or
exhaustion.</def> <mark>[Colloq.]</mark> <rj><au>G. Eliot.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>What is called <qex>seediness</qex>, after a debauch, is a plain
proof that nature has been outraged.</q> <rj><qau>J. S.
Blackie.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Seed-lac</ent>⟦br⟧
